page.title: 14FINTRY:Population.Background
page.content: This is a summation of interesting facts to enhance information in pages: { North Population {West East }: FINTRY { South Total population 737,(259 households). Children under sixteen 170, older children in education or training 56. Of 336 workers 47 are part-time,1 man. Local employers are about 25not counting 18 farms with 13 workers, usually sons. Also 13 retired farmers. The proximity of Glasgow and Stirling account for the high number in medical and educational work 59. Building and engineering 28. clerical 19 women. A{marked feature}is the wide range of jobs within these categories and also in{addition}we have: a stockbroker, a librarian, a trombonist,a solicitor, an immigration officer, a lorry driver and a brewer - (Cheers! Editor).
